Program: Outlook
Title: Outlook
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00m2wxq
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 19 Dec 2011
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world. All of this week, Outlook is broadcasting from New Delhi, marking 100 years since the city became the capital of modern India. In this edition, Gaurav Saini tells Matthew Bannister about his struggle to find out what happened to his beloved bride Monika Dagar who died just a month after their forbidden wedding. Sminu Jindal, granddaughter of the founder of one of India's biggest companies, describes how the childhood accident that left her disabled has spurred her on to be a high achiever in the family business. And the Delhiwalla, Mayank Austen Soofi shares stories from the street in his mission to interview one per cent of Delhi's fourteen million inhabitants. Show less